The objective function of this model is to minimize the total cost of the energy system while meeting the energy demand and constraints. The investment and dismantling costs are transformed into streams of annual payments, computed for each year of the horizon. Using China-ESPT, a total net present value (NPV) of the stream of annual costs is then computed, discounted to a user-selected reference year. The objective function of the model is listed in Eqs. (1)–(2):1OBJ(z)=∑r∈REGNPV(z,r),\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
